summary: This is an email chain between US Attorney's Office for the Southern District of New York (USANYS) personnel and an FBI Special Agent, discussing case file requests. The FBI agent provides documentation of Jeffrey Epstein's phone number and last call made, and the prosecutors discuss requesting the FBI's entire SENTRY file and all 302s to ensure they have complete information.

persons.name: Special Agent
persons.context: FBI Special Agent from the New York Field Office Violent Crimes Task Force who provided documentation of Epstein's phone number and last call made to the US Attorney's Office.

events.title: Case File Coordination Email
events.description: Email exchange between the US Attorney's Office and the FBI regarding documentation of Jeffrey Epstein's phone records and case file requests.

keyFacts: The FBI Special Agent documented Jeffrey Epstein's phone number and the last call he made.
Prosecutors from the US Attorney's Office for the Southern District of New York are discussing requesting the FBI's entire SENTRY file to ensure they have all case materials.
There is uncertainty about whether all FBI 302 interview reports had been previously requested, prompting consideration to request them again.
